dct_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Ljubljana, sheet Y-2.. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413)
dct_description_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Ljubljana. Lambert conical orthomorphic projection. Nord de Guerre grid. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. Reproduced under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service, U.S. Army, Washington, D.C. 1944, from Kodalines of GSGS First Edition (Army/Air) 1944, compiled and drawn by War office, 1944. With German, Serb and Croat glossaries. Intelligence reports up to Nov. 1943. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete. Geographic designation is given as Yugoslavia it is Slovenia.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
